[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(2-5) David gathers craftsmen, and accumulates materials for building the house of God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(2) And David commanded to gather together the strangers.—The word rendered “to gather together” (kānas) is different from the terms used in 1Chronicles 15:3-4; 1Chronicles 19:7, and is late in this sense.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(2) ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And David commanded to gather together the strangers.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The word rendered “to gather together” (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "kānas",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ") is different from the terms used in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 15:3-4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 19:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", and is late in this sense.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The strangers (gêrîm).—Sojourners, or resident foreigners, such as Israel had been in Egypt (Genesis 15:13). The Canaanite population are meant, who lived on sufferance under the Israelite dominion, and were liable to forced service if the government required it. (See 2Chronicles 8:7-8, and 1Kings 9:20-21.) Solomon found them by census to be 153,600 souls. The census was a preliminary to apportioning their several tasks. (See 2Chronicles 2:17-18.) David, probably on the present occasion, had held a similar census of the Canaanite serfs (2Chronicles 2:17).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The strangers",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "gêrîm",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ")",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": ".—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Sojourners, or resident foreigners, such as Israel had been in Egypt (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 15:13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "). The Canaanite population are meant, who lived on sufferance under the Israelite dominion, and were liable to forced service if the government required it. (See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 8:7-8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", and ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Kings 9:20-21",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) Solomon found them by census to be 153,600 souls. The census was a preliminary to apportioning their several tasks. (See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 2:17-18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) David, probably on the present occasion, had held a similar census of the Canaanite serfs (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Chronicles 2:17",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ").",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And he set.—Appointed (1Chronicles 15:16-17); literally, caused to stand.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And he set.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Appointed",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 15:16-17",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "); literally, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "caused to stand.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Masons.—Hewers; selected, apparently, from among “the strangers.”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Masons.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Hewers",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; selected, apparently, from among “the strangers.”",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Wrought stones.—“Saxum quadratum,” square stones (1 Kings 5:31; Isaiah 9:9).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Wrought stones.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—“Saxum quadratum,” square stones (1 Kings 5:31; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Isaiah 9:9",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ").",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "To build the house—i.e., for building it hereafter. It is not said that the work was begun at once, but only that the organisation of the serf labour originated with David.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "To build the house",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—i.e., for building it hereafter. It is not said that the work was begun at once, but only that the organisation of the serf labour originated with David.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
